Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and peel the @shallot{1/2}. Chop half into small pieces.

Finely chop the @chives{5%g} (use scissors if you prefer).

Peel and trim the @carrot{1}, then halve lengthways. Chop into roughly
1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Finely chop the @smoked salmon{100%g}. > IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils
after handling raw salmon.

Cut half the @tortilla{4} into triangles (like pizza slices).

Place on a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}
and toss to coat.

Arrange in a single layer (use two trays if necessary).

Bake in the #oven{} until crispy and golden, ~{6-8%minutes} (Keep an eye on
them so they don't burn).

To a #bowl{}, add the smoked salmon, @creme fraiche{110%g}, chives and
1 tsp shallot.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Mix well to combine.

Serve the smoked salmon dip with carrot batons and tortilla chips alongside.